## Desk Save/Load\
\
- [ ] Place Save Desk button at the bottom of the sidebar, just above Change Theme controls. Clicking it opens a popup with options to save the current desk state, load previous saves, or delete saves. This keeps global layout actions grouped together and easy to find without cluttering the workspace.\
\
- [ ] Add save/load feature for entire desk state (stickers, reminders, todos, calendar, clock) via in-app popup. Users can create named save slots (e.g., \'93Morning Setup\'94), stored in localStorage, and reload or delete saves later. Optionally add Export/Import for portability. No computer file access required.\
\
- [ ] Add option for reminders and to-dos to be saved with desk state. By default, all items are included when saving/loading. Provide checkbox in save popup to optionally exclude reminders/todos if user wants a clean slate desk layout without tasks.\
\
- [ ] Add option to transfer reminders and to-dos when creating a new desk layout. By default, desk saves capture stickers, positions, and widgets. Provide checkbox in popup to keep existing reminders/todos in the new desk, so users can experiment with layouts without losing their tasks.\
